ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS

Tumult is inspired by and builds upon the concepts pioneered by the
Chaos Toolkit project (https://chaostoolkit.org/).

Chaos Toolkit is an open-source chaos engineering platform created by
Russ Miles and the ChaosIQ team, licensed under the Apache License 2.0.
https://github.com/chaostoolkit/chaostoolkit

Tumult's experiment model — including the concepts of steady-state
hypothesis, method (actions and probes), rollbacks, controls, and the
declarative experiment format — is directly inspired by Chaos Toolkit's
pioneering work in making chaos engineering accessible and standardized.

We are grateful to the Chaos Toolkit community for establishing the
foundational patterns that Tumult reimagines in Rust with TOON format
and OpenTelemetry-first observability.

